-- CTC Media’s CTC TV Russia Audience Shrinks, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-06-22T15:16:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-22/ctc-media-s-ctc-tv-russia-audience-shrinks-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel fell to the seventh most-watched among Russian viewers
18 years and older in the week to June 17, from fifth a week
before, as its audience dropped, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, fell to 5.1 percent, from
5.3 percent in the week to June 10, data researcher TNS-Global
said by e-mail yesterday.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over fell to 5.7 percent in the week to June 17 from 6.1 percent
in the week to June 10, the data show. CTC remained in fifth
place among viewers 4 years old and over, TNS-Global said.  Russia’s Pervyi Kanal was the most watched among both
audience categories, pushing NTV Television to second in both
segments. Government-controlled Rossiya-1 was the third-most
watched in both categories and TNT TV was fourth, the data show.  REN TV and Fifth Channel outpaced CTC among Russian viewers
18 years old and older in the week to June 17, becoming the
fifth- and sixth-most watched, the data show.  To contact the reporters on this story:
